      <akn:section eId="sec_22_3223">
        <akn:num>22-3223</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Credit card fraud.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3223_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>For the purposes of this section, the term “credit card” means an instrument or device, whether known as a credit card, debit card, or by any other name, issued for use of the cardholder in obtaining or paying for property or services.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3223_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A person commits the offense of credit card fraud if, with intent to defraud, that person obtains or pays for property or services by:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3223_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A credit card is deemed cancelled or revoked when notice in writing thereof has been received by the named holder as shown on the credit card or by the records of the issuer.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3223_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
